1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

2
00:00:03,240 --> 00:00:04,900
 All right, good morning, guys.

3
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:05,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

4
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,680
 Very good to see you all.

5
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:12,480
 And as you know, I came back from Turkey last--

6
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:12,980
 Saturday.

7
00:00:12,980 --> 00:00:13,480
 Saturday.

8
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:14,800
 Yeah, last Saturday.

9
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:20,200
 So I'm trying to reorient myself back to the Chicago time.

10
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:29,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

11
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:31,000
 So next time, if you have the opportunity,

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,720
 you should come to the Bible Lens with me.

13
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:38,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

14
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:42,720
 OK, so last week, I shared with you

15
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:46,360
 my recent trip, some of the highlights from my Turkey trip.

16
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:50,280
 And it's about the first missionary journey of Paul,

17
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,600
 recorded in the Book of Acts.

18
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,240
 And we visit different biblical sites

19
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:57,200
 that will help us understand the context of scripture.

20
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,680
 So today, I want to bring you another highlight, which

21
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,800
 is a place called Leuticia.

22
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:15,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

23
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,720
 And this place is called Leuticia.

24
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:21,480
 And you can find the text from the Book of Revelation,

25
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:25,280
 the last book of the Bible, chapter 3, 14 to 22.

26
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:31,240
 And as you can see from this Google Maps screen cap,

27
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:33,520
 Leuticia, in terms of background,

28
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,400
 was a very, very wealthy city.

29
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:39,760
 Now, as you hear about the context of Leuticia,

30
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,880
 you can think of it's kind of like Chicago, OK?

31
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,520
 So it was a traffic hub.

32
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,720
 It was the center of all the traffic east and west

33
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,200
 and north and south.

34
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,720
 And the banking center, right?

35
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,580
 Sound like our city, right?

36
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,880
 And it was also, in the ancient time,

37
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,240
 a center of textile production.

38
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:59,720
 So they produced a lot of clothing

39
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:04,520
 and a lot of good wool or sheepskin.

40
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:08,560
 And it's also, interestingly, a place well-known

41
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:12,120
 for its medical treatment.

42
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:15,240
 So if you go to the hospital, especially for your eyes,

43
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:19,680
 eye medicine, it was a very well-known thing in Leuticia.

44
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:23,640
 So outwardly, this city, Leuticia, and its culture

45
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:26,120
 look very, very strong and very successful

46
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,440
 and very self-sufficient.

47
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

48
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:56,840
 But as you turn to the text today, Revelation 3,

49
00:02:56,840 --> 00:03:02,400
 you see when Jesus spoke to the church in Leuticia,

50
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:06,020
 he saw something very different from how they see themselves.

51
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:10,240
 And what looked healthy, what looked successful to them,

52
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:13,560
 is actually very sick on the inside.

53
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:17,720
 And when they looked rich, but they are actually

54
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,720
 poor in the eyes of Jesus.

55
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:23,600
 When they looked strong, they were actually pretty weak

56
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,440
 in the sight of God.

57
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

58
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:37,640
 So even though it looks very, very successful,

59
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:40,600
 very self-sufficient, you look at the letter,

60
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,800
 and it says--

61
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:46,840
 and we can read from chapter 3, 14 and following--

62
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:50,320
 "To the angel of the church in Leuticia write,

63
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:53,280
 these are the words of the Amen--"

64
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:56,800
 and Jesus called himself Amen because it means truthful--

65
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:00,480
 "the faithful and true witness and the ruler

66
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,040
 of God's creation.

67
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:09,360
 15, I know your deeds, and that you are neither cold nor hot.

68
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:12,880
 I wish you were either one or the other.

69
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:17,440
 So because you are lukewarm, neither hot nor cold,

70
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:21,240
 I am about to spit you out of my mouth."

71
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

72
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:47,200
 So Jesus says to the church, you are neither cold nor hot.

73
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:50,080
 Sometimes we approach this statement,

74
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,400
 and we think that, OK, these are, of course,

75
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,440
 very serious words.

76
00:04:53,440 --> 00:05:01,840
 And we only think that hot, meaning spiritually passionate.

77
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:05,840
 And then cold, meaning, of course, to us, cold water

78
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,840
 or cold hearted.

79
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,920
 It may mean, OK, they are spiritually detached

80
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:15,360
 or distant, but the local geography of Leuticia,

81
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:18,200
 of this city, will help us understand this passage

82
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,880
 or those words better.

83
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:23,680
 Because when you turn to the map,

84
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:28,040
 you see Leuticia is right in the middle, right?

85
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:31,000
 And then north of it is someplace

86
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:39,200
 called [INAUDIBLE] today, or Hierapolis.

87
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,880
 That is in the north, right?

88
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:45,680
 And that is the place known for hot spring or hot water spring,

89
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:49,480
 still having mineral water, hot water coming out

90
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:53,440
 of this place, which is north of Leuticia.

91
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:56,400
 And to the right is Colossae.

92
00:05:56,400 --> 00:06:01,160
 And Colossae was known for its cold mountain, cold spring

93
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,320
 water.

94
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:05,920
 And both hot water and cold water were very useful.

95
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,720
 You see that?

96
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:32,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

97
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:39,960
 So when I went there, this is Hierapolis, right?

98
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:44,520
 So I was actually there, even though it feels like--

99
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:47,040
 or it looks like there was a green screen.

100
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:48,960
 And I keyed myself in there.

101
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:51,160
 But it was a very, very beautiful place.

102
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,040
 And it's all white.

103
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:57,980
 And [SPEAKING CHINESE] actually means cotton castle.

104
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:01,440
 And it gets the name because from afar,

105
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:06,440
 you look at Pamukkale, it looks white at the mountaintop.

106
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:09,400
 And it has hot spring really coming out today.

107
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:13,580
 And you can go there and enjoy it on barefoot.

108
00:07:13,580 --> 00:07:19,240
 And that is Pamukkale or Hierapolis.

109
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:24,800
 And Leoticia is a little bit different.

110
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:28,080
 Leoticia, right in the middle, it

111
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,800
 drew water from springs to the south.

112
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,980
 But by the time the warm water or hot water

113
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:37,880
 reached the city through the water pipe,

114
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:41,080
 the water became mineral-laden.

115
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:46,120
 And because you got some white stuff in your water.

116
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,680
 And it doesn't taste very good.

117
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:50,920
 And that is the image of lukewarm water

118
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,520
 for Leoticia.

119
00:07:52,520 --> 00:08:19,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

120
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:24,560
 So the water in Leoticia is kind of like what we call hot water.

121
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:28,760
 I know Chicago is known for hot water.

122
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,600
 Because some people complain to me they do a shower

123
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:35,020
 and they wash their hairs, they lose hairs.

124
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,120
 Because hot water.

125
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,040
 Because you got minerals in your--

126
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:41,040
 there is stuff in the water.

127
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,720
 And it's not refreshing.

128
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:46,920
 And it's not refreshing like cold water, Colossi.

129
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,880
 It's not refreshing or therapeutic

130
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:53,120
 like the hot water in Hierapolis.

131
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:59,560
 And the water in Leoticia was simply distasteful and useless.

132
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:18,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

133
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:23,000
 I find some water pipe in the ancient time.

134
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:29,960
 And it was deposited with some sort of what we call calcium

135
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:34,240
 carbonate, some of the deposit from the mineral from the water.

136
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,240
 And as you can tell, the quality of water in Leoticia

137
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:40,200
 is very, very poor.

138
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:45,900
 So Jesus is not speaking about when he says cold or hot.

139
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:51,480
 He's not talking about our spiritual temperature for God.

140
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:54,960
 And he's speaking about usefulness for God.

141
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:59,360
 So hot water or hot spring water is useful.

142
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,720
 Because you can dump yourself in there

143
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,920
 and you can enjoy the hot spring, right?

144
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,600
 And the cold water, of course, is useful.

145
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,760
 You can drink it.

146
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,800
 But the lukewarm water in Leoticia

147
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,800
 was useless, totally useless.

148
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,560
 Because you cannot use it.

149
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:15,680
 And in the same way, Jesus is referring

150
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:19,840
 to the Christians in Leoticia that they

151
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:23,560
 have become useless for God's purpose.

152
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:50,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

153
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:53,760
 So this message will help us to understand the words

154
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:56,760
 in the letter to Leoticia.

155
00:10:56,760 --> 00:11:00,940
 And the message is for us today as well.

156
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:06,240
 Because we can be successful in the sight of the world

157
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,640
 by human standards.

158
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:12,400
 Yet we can be spiritually ineffective or useless to God.

159
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,920
 And the Christian can be respectable,

160
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,720
 can be successful.

161
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:22,280
 But in the sight of God, it's not truly useful.

162
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:35,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

163
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,920
 So the question is, how can we become

164
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,640
 useful for God's purpose?

165
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:42,880
 And we look at at least three points from this passage.

166
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:48,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

167
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,160
 First, we need to understand this short letter.

168
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:56,040
 Jesus Christ is desiring for something from us, from you.

169
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:58,480
 It's a fruitful relationship with you.

170
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:03,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

171
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:07,240
 And Jesus does not look at our money.

172
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,920
 Jesus does not look at our success.

173
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:12,560
 Now, we check our portfolio every day, right?

174
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:16,400
 We check our bank account, especially tax season.

175
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:20,200
 We check how much money we have and our ability.

176
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:26,360
 But Jesus looks at us as whether we are abiding in him,

177
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:29,960
 whether we are building a living and fruitful relationship

178
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:30,720
 with him.

179
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,400
 And being useful, being fruitful,

180
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:35,960
 begins with our fellowship with Jesus.

181
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:48,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

182
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:52,920
 Now, the problem with the seer was not that they had money.

183
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:55,440
 The problem-- they had money, that's fine.

184
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,760
 The problem is that they no longer

185
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:01,960
 felt that they needed Christ when they are rich.

186
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:05,240
 Their wealth had made them so self-sufficient,

187
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:08,000
 and they don't need God.

188
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:14,000
 And they have comfort, and that would weaken their relationship

189
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,880
 or dependence on the Lord.

190
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:29,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

191
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,880
 Now, you think about it.

192
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:34,280
 This can happen to all of us, right?

193
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:36,120
 This can happen to all of us.

194
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,880
 We may still come to church.

195
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:43,080
 We may still serve, or we look outside, from the outside.

196
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,120
 We look faithful.

197
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:51,240
 But inwardly, we may not be depending on Jesus deeply.

198
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:54,240
 And we may be active, but we are not

199
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:58,000
 abiding in him, having a living relationship with God.

200
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:15,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

201
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:19,440
 But if we want to be useful for the purpose of God,

202
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:23,680
 first and foremost, we must stay close to Christ.

203
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:25,160
 Stay close to Christ.

204
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,400
 We must walk with him, and listen to him,

205
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,360
 and depend on him, and love him.

206
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,240
 This is a fruitful life, and that

207
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,520
 will continue to grow out of your living relationship

208
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,160
 with God.

209
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:39,240
 And you become useful for God's purpose.

210
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:53,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

211
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:58,120
 And then the second point here, Christ desires to dwell in your heart.

212
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:01,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

213
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,680
 Verse 17, it says, "You say," speaking

214
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:07,160
 to the Christians in Laodicea, self-sufficient Christians,

215
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:08,840
 "You say, I am rich.

216
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:12,400
 I have acquired wealth and do not need a thing.

217
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:18,880
 But you do not realize that you are wretched, pitiful, poor, blind,

218
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,080
 and naked."

219
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:25,600
 So Jesus said to the church, "I counsel you to buy me gold

220
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,400
 we find in the fire."

221
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:30,800
 Now, you said you have gold, but you don't really have gold.

222
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:34,280
 You have to buy gold from me we find in the fire

223
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:37,200
 so you can become rich.

224
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:41,760
 And you get the white clothes to wear so that you

225
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:44,400
 can cover your shameful nakedness.

226
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:50,080
 And then you can put ointment on your eyes so that you can see.

227
00:15:50,080 --> 00:16:14,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

228
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:24,800
 So as you can see from the context,

229
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:28,560
 Jesus is using the very thing the city of the people

230
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:32,920
 were proud of to expose their true poor condition.

231
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:36,640
 And they were proud of their banking, proud of their gold

232
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:40,940
 and riches, but they were actually poor spiritually.

233
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:43,920
 And that they were proud of their textile, their clothing,

234
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:47,560
 their industry, but they were actually naked spiritually.

235
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,880
 They were proud of their eye medicine,

236
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,400
 but they were actually spiritually blind.

237
00:16:52,400 --> 00:17:11,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

238
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:15,720
 And this is a warning to all of us, right?

239
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:19,480
 It's possible for us to be outwardly successful.

240
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:25,240
 Outwardly, we get everything self-sufficient.

241
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:28,000
 But inwardly, we can be empty.

242
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,600
 And it is possible for us to gain many things in life,

243
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,880
 but we are still missing the most important thing.

244
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:35,800
 And what matters most is that the presence of Christ

245
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,320
 in our hearts.

246
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:49,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

247
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:53,160
 That's why Jesus said, I cancel you.

248
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:53,920
 You listen to me.

249
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:55,740
 You buy gold from me.

250
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:57,960
 You buy white cloths from me.

251
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:00,400
 And you put on your eyes ointment from me

252
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,360
 so that you can see.

253
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,720
 In other words, what truly is needed

254
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:08,380
 could only come from Jesus Christ our Lord.

255
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:20,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

256
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,440
 And pay attention to this.

257
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:28,000
 Only, only Christ can make you truly rich.

258
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:33,160
 And only Christ can cover your shame, your sin.

259
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:35,400
 Only Christ can open our eyes.

260
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,640
 Only Christ can make us whole.

261
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:50,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

262
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,760
 And the third point here, the letter says,

263
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:54,800
 Jesus is calling you to repentance

264
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,240
 and to renew fellowship with him.

265
00:18:57,240 --> 00:19:04,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE] Now, verses 19 and following,

266
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:08,680
 it says, those whom I love, I rebuild and discipline.

267
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:12,440
 So be earnest and repent.

268
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,040
 And these are very, very strong words.

269
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:17,400
 Actually, among the seven letters,

270
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,720
 this one, the last one to live this year,

271
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:22,000
 is the strongest letter.

272
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,880
 But you listen to the words.

273
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:26,800
 They are actually words of love.

274
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,400
 Because Jesus rebuilds his church

275
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,960
 not because he has given up on them.

276
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,960
 It's just because he still loves them.

277
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:53,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

278
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:55,920
 And in verse 20, he continues.

279
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,640
 Jesus says, here I am.

280
00:19:57,640 --> 00:20:01,080
 I'm standing at the door, and I'm knocking.

281
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:04,160
 And this is a moving picture.

282
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:08,120
 The church is trying to push Jesus to the outside,

283
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,960
 trying to etch him out.

284
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:13,920
 And yet Jesus was still standing there and still knocking

285
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,000
 and still calling them back.

286
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:30,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

287
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:34,880
 And Jesus says, if anyone hears my voice and opens the door,

288
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:41,320
 I will come in, and I will eat with him, and he be with me.

289
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:46,160
 Now, in the ancient world, especially in the ancient eastern world,

290
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:48,800
 sharing a meal together or sharing a table

291
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,440
 was a picture of close relationship.

292
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:54,240
 And Jesus is offering something so intimate

293
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:57,120
 to restore our communion with him.

294
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:13,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

295
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,760
 Now, this means if the leviticus is reminding you

296
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,960
 you are lukewarm today, remember it's not

297
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:21,240
 your spiritual temperature.

298
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:24,080
 If you're lukewarm today, it means in God's sight,

299
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:27,240
 we are not that useful, right?

300
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,960
 We're not that close to him.

301
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:32,320
 The answer to lukewarmness, all right,

302
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:36,560
 lukewarmness of our heart condition is not trying harder.

303
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:38,680
 It's not doing more things.

304
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:43,600
 The answer is opening the door again to Christ our Lord.

305
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:46,880
 And it is turning back to him.

306
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:51,720
 It's making room, opening the door to dwell with him

307
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:55,200
 so that Christ can dwell at the center of our lives again.

308
00:21:55,200 --> 00:22:10,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

309
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:14,840
 Now, some of us, some of us here may not

310
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,640
 have rejected Jesus openly, right?

311
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,880
 We're not anti-Jesus.

312
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:24,200
 But perhaps we have slowly drifted away from him.

313
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,720
 And we still know the language of faith,

314
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:30,760
 but we no longer live in a close fellowship with him.

315
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:33,800
 And yet, today, from this letter,

316
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:39,240
 Jesus is still knocking at your door.

317
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:53,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

318
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,520
 So if you think about it, you know, Charlie, reflect.

319
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:59,080
 Jesus may have been still knocking on your door.

320
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:02,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

321
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:08,120
 He is calling us back, and not to shame us, but to restore us.

322
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,720
 He wants to renew our heart, come into our hearts,

323
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:14,680
 renew our vision, and renew our usefulness for God's purpose.

324
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:21,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

325
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:24,480
 So the message to the Christians and the seer

326
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:27,360
 is also a message to all of us.

327
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:33,920
 Do not be content, do not be content with our comfort

328
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:37,360
 while inwardly we're drifting away from Christ.

329
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,400
 Do not trust in our own strengths,

330
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:41,720
 and do not say, I don't need a thing from God.

331
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:54,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

332
00:23:54,280 --> 00:24:01,240
 Instead, today, we turn to Jesus and abide in him.

333
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:06,800
 Open your hearts to him, and let him search you,

334
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:09,400
 heal you, and restore you.

335
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:13,240
 And this is how we become useful for God's purpose.

336
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:22,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

337
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:25,600
 Now, at the end of this letter is a series

338
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:27,440
 of words of comfort.

339
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,560
 Jesus gives us promise at the end.

340
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:33,560
 To him who overcomes, to him who is faithful,

341
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:38,520
 I will give the right to sit with me on my throne.

342
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:44,160
 You see, this is invitation of grace, invitation of hope.

343
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,120
 And what an invitation, right?

344
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:48,640
 We etch him out, but he's knocking on our door.

345
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:52,880
 And Christ not only wants us, he welcomes us.

346
00:24:52,880 --> 00:25:05,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

347
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:11,120
 May God keep us from being lukewarm, being useless.

348
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:14,440
 May he make us, all of us, to be close to him

349
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:18,080
 and full of grace and repentance.

350
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:20,320
 And truly, we want to be useful.

351
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:22,960
 We want to be pleasant for God's purpose.

352
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:32,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

353
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:37,360
 Now, at this point, we want to have some quiet moment.

354
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:40,840
 And I want to invite you to speak to the Lord who

355
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,920
 is knocking on your door.

356
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:56,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

357
00:25:56,440 --> 00:26:02,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

358
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:06,320
 Let's spend some time and pray together, and I will close.

359
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:34,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

360
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:34,640
 Let's pray.

361
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:37,760
 Heavenly Father, we thank you for speaking to us

362
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,800
 through your Word today.

363
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:44,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

364
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:47,680
 Forgive us for the times we have become self-sufficient,

365
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:50,560
 lukewarm, and detached from Christ.

366
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:57,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

367
00:26:57,160 --> 00:27:01,440
 So draw us back to you today into a living and fruitful

368
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:03,200
 relationship with you.

369
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:07,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

370
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:10,520
 And dear God, we ask that you open our eyes

371
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:13,120
 to see our true condition.

372
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:16,440
 And we want to welcome Jesus more fully into our hearts.

373
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:24,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

374
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:28,360
 And Jesus, do make us a people who are close to you

375
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:31,440
 and quick to repent and useful for your purpose.

376
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:37,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

377
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:39,920
 And we pray all this in Jesus' name.

378
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

379
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:44,480
 Amen.

380
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,280
 Well, may God bless you all, and I

381
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,600
 want to see you next week.

382
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:52,320
 And become useful to desire a better relationship with God

383
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:54,040
 and to worship him, OK?

384
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:58,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

385
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:01,000
 And I know Patrick has--

